heaviest_rainfall.status: Ranked 7th for total rainfall, today's storm had precipitation totalling 23.86mm, falling at 8.3mm per hour at times during the 31.0 hour long storm.  Record-breaking rain fell on 09 November 2025 with a total accumulation of 47.89mm over 144.8 hours and falling at a rate of 24.6mm per hour at times.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 27.6mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 2nd from our records.  The precipitation lasted 1.8 hours and dumped 4.92mm in total.  The heaviest rain was recorded on 02 September 2025 with a peak rate of 34.3mm per hour.  The storm lasted 15.0 hours and had a total rainfall of 21.19mm.

longest_rain.status: The storm today ranked 7th for the length of the storm when compared to others in our records and it lasted 31.0 hours.  23.86mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 8.3mm per hour.  On 09 November 2025, the rain lasted for 144.8 hours, which is the longest time recorded by our database.  47.89mm accumulated and it fell at 24.6mm per hour at times.
